  <body id="msgFeedSummaryBody" selected="false">
    <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p>When you change themes on a Drupal 7 site, you often need to reset the placement of your blocks. If you're using the core block module to place them, you may end up with a bunch of blocks in unexpected places on your new theme.  If you want to reset everything and start from scratch, you could edit the {blocks} table in your database, but you can also do it with JavaScript.  While viewing the blocks admin page (admin/structure/blocks), paste this line into your JavaScript console:</p>

<p><code lang="js" xml:lang="js">
jQuery('#blocks').find('select').val(-1);
</code></p></div></div></div><div class="field field-name-node-link field-type-ds field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><a href="/buzz/drupal-javascript-snippet-reset-block-placement-to-none">Read more</a></div></div></div>
